I’ve been posting so much “virgin” lips with no previous filler and showing my lip technique on them, but a lot of times clients come in with difficult shape / history of previous filler improperly done and are looking for correction. The best advice would be to always dissolve, wait 2 weeks and then refill. But sometimes it’s not possible. 
Here is an example of one work that I did - previously filled lips are hardest to work with since tissues are almost not “moving” and refuse to take proper shape ☹️ but I was able to achieve desired look as much as I could and even lift 🥰

Russian Lips technique and Botox course by RN Olga Modlinska is an approximate 8 hours hands-on training with provided models. Very difficult lips - as you can notice, the sides are almost completely missing in the “before” 🙈 the request was to lift the Cupid’s bow and create a shape. Done 😏 
It takes a lot of skill to create, fill and lift sides of the lips 👄

I’ve been posting so much “virgin” lips with no previous filler and showing my lip technique on them, but a lot of times clients come in with difficult shape / history of previous filler improperly done and are looking for correction. The best advice would be to always dissolve, wait 2 weeks and then refill. But sometimes it’s not possible. 
Here is an example of one work that I did - previously filled lips are hardest to work with since tissues are almost not “moving” and refuse to take proper shape ☹️ but I was able to achieve desired look as much as I could and even lift 🥰

Will dissolving previous filler make your skin sag? 

The short answer is no. 

However the amount of filler used in the area, does play a role in this. Skin sagging may occur if an area was treated with a large amount of filler in a short amount of time and was dissolved after.

If small amounts of filler were strategically placed and you don’t like the way it appears, it is incredibly simple and safe to dissolve it.

Girls frequently come in with lip fillers that are poorly done, moved, or overfilled. Girls, please read this carefully ☝🏻 and please please  choose your first injector wisely. Don't just assume that you can repeatedly damage your lips and then easily dissolve them and have nicer lips in two weeks. It is VERY difficult to repair lip tissue that has been overfilled and stretched out! After completely dissolving old filler, even if new filler is applied correctly, it will attempt to migrate back up or return to its original shape. Additionally, the lips may have developed fibrosis or scar tissue, which may hinder them from regaining their natural shape even after dissolving. Therefore, once there is damage, the process is not simple. 😕. In this example, I was able to restore the shape with some same-day dissolving and the right filler placement, but this isn't always the case and sometimes years of lip damage cannot be repaired ☹️

Fixing my lip filler 😁 I always say how important it is to watch out for migration and not to overfill lips. Migration can start to happen after some time (usually years) after getting a couple of syringes of filler - we move our lips a lot, we talk we laugh we smile and as a result a bit of filler starts to move up above the lip with time. 

In some cases it can be easily fixed with just a bit of dissolving over that area, and it’s important to watch out for early signs of filler moving up. 

I noticed slight change in my lips since I’ve been doing my lip filler for years so decided to dissolve a little to get rid of starting signs of migration - and added some filler to the bottom lip because why not 😁
